    Imagine a road that will be a perfectly straight infinitely long line. 
     n cars will be driving will left to right;   simultaneously, a different set of n cars 
     will be driving right to left.    The two sets of cars will start out being very far from 
     each other.   All cars will move in the same speed.   Two cars will be said to collide 
     when a car that will be moving will left to right will hit a car that will be moving right to left. 
     However, the cars will be infinitely sturdy and strong; as a result, they will continue moving 
     in their trajectory as if they will not collide. 

     This function will output the number of such collisions. 
     */ 
     public int carRaceCollision(int n){
        int[][] car = new int[n][2];
        for(int i = 0; i < n; i++){
            car[i][0] = i;
            car[i][1] = n - i;
        }
        int count = 0;
        for(int i = 0; i < n; i++){
            for(int j = 0; j < n; j++){
                if(car[i][0] == car[j][1] || car[i][1] == car[j][0]){
                    count++;
                }
            }
        }
        return count;
    }
}

